Mock SOC 2 Internal Audit Report
Company:
TechNova Solutions
Audit Title:
SOC 2 – Logical Access Controls Audit
Trust Services Criteria (TSC):
Security
Audit Period:
March 1 – March 15, 2026
Auditor:
Travis Hull – GRC Analyst
1. Objective
The objective of this audit was to assess whether logical access controls at TechNova Solutions are designed and operating effectively to meet SOC 2 Security Trust Services Criteria related to user access, authentication, and authorization.

2. Scope
This audit focused on logical access controls supporting:
User provisioning and deprovisioning
Role-based access control (RBAC)
Privileged access management
Periodic access reviews
Systems Reviewed:
Identity & Access Management (IAM) system
Internal SaaS applications
HR onboarding/offboarding records

3. Applicable SOC 2 Criteria
The following SOC 2 Trust Services Criteria were evaluated:
CC6.1: Logical access security software, infrastructure, and architectures are implemented
CC6.2: Prior to issuing system credentials, access is authorized and documented
CC6.3: Access is removed when no longer required
CC6.6: Logical access security measures are implemented to protect against unauthorized access

4. Methodology
The audit was conducted using the following procedures:
Reviewed access control and security policies
Sampled 15 user accounts across departments
Inspected onboarding and termination records
Evaluated user roles and privilege assignments
Assessed evidence of periodic access reviews
Mapped controls to SOC 2 Trust Services Criteria

5. Control Testing & Results
Control 1: User Deprovisioning (CC6.3)
Control Description:
User access is removed promptly upon employee termination.
Test Performed:
Reviewed 15 terminated user accounts and compared termination dates to access removal dates.
Result: ❌ Failed
Observation:
3 users retained access beyond 7 days after termination.
Control 2: Access Authorization (CC6.2)
Control Description:
User access is approved and documented prior to provisioning.
Test Performed:
Reviewed onboarding records for approval documentation.
Result: ✅ Passed
Observation:
All sampled users had documented approval before access was granted.
Control 3: Least Privilege Enforcement (CC6.1 / CC6.6)
Control Description:
Access is restricted based on job responsibilities.
Test Performed:
Reviewed user roles and privileges for appropriateness.
Result: ⚠️ Partially Effective
Observation:
Some users had administrative access beyond job requirements.
Control 4: Periodic Access Reviews (CC6.1)
Control Description:
Management performs periodic reviews of user access.
Test Performed:
Requested evidence of quarterly access reviews.
Result: ❌ Failed
Observation:
No documented evidence of formal access reviews.

6. Findings & Recommendations
Finding 1: Delayed User Deprovisioning (CC6.3)
Risk Level: High
Risk: Unauthorized system access post-termination
Recommendation: Automate deprovisioning via HR system integration
Finding 2: Excessive Privileges (CC6.1 / CC6.6)
Risk Level: Medium
Risk: Increased risk of misuse or system changes
Recommendation: Enforce least privilege and implement role reviews
Finding 3: Lack of Access Reviews (CC6.1)
Risk Level: Medium
Risk: Undetected inappropriate access
Recommendation: Implement quarterly access certification process

7. Positive Observations
Documented access control policies are in place
Multi-factor authentication (MFA) is enforced
Access approval process is consistently followed

8. Conclusion
TechNova Solutions has implemented key logical access controls aligned with SOC 2 Security criteria. However, deficiencies in deprovisioning and access review processes indicate that certain controls are not operating effectively. Remediation of these issues will strengthen compliance posture and reduce access-related risks.

9. Risk Summary
Finding	SOC 2 Criteria	Risk Level
Delayed Deprovisioning	CC6.3	High
Excessive Privileges	CC6.1 / CC6.6	Medium
No Access Reviews	CC6.1	Medium
